        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 8 at 3:32PM CDT until June 8 at 3:45PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 331 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Oak Brook,
moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Clarendon Hills, Hinsdale, Darien, Oak Brook, Woodridge, Downers
Grove, Burr Ridge, Oakbrook Terrace, Willowbrook, Westmont, York
Center, Glen Ellyn, Lisle, Willow Springs, Lombard, and Bolingbrook.
</description>
        <instruction>Prepare immediately for large hail and damaging winds. People outside
should move to a shelter, inside a strong building and away from
windows.</instruction>
